    "These developments contribute to the improved performance and applicability of AI in sensory analysis systems.",
    "AI-backed systems, such as electronic noses (Moshayedi et al. 2023) (Moshayedi et al. 2025) and tongues (Tan and Xu 2020), have shown remarkable abilities.",
    "They map molecular structures to sensory responses, detect differences in flavor profiles, and predict consumer preferences.",
    "Figure 1 illustrates the interaction between odor and taste in the context of AI-driven analysis.",
    "Odorants and tastants are represented as molecular data, which are processed through both the physiological sensory systems (such as the nose and tongue) and AI algorithms."
